# (disabled - trace logging not active)
#
# /tmp/vpn-switch-trace.log
#
# Debug trace file - logs command execution flow (dispatch, interpreter resolution, output)

USAGE:
  Set this variable to enable detailed execution tracing for debugging.

  Environment variable (one-time):
    VPN_SWITCH_TRACE_FILE=/tmp/trace.log vpn-switch wireguard start privacy

  Persistent configuration (.env/local/VPN_SWITCH_TRACE_FILE):
    Uncomment the path above: /tmp/vpn-switch-trace.log

  Disable tracing (three ways):
    1. Leave empty (blank line)
    2. Use comment line starting with #
    3. Remove/unset the variable

    All three are treated as "unset" by build_env_args()

OUTPUT FORMAT:
  Each trace entry includes:
  - Timestamp
  - Command being executed
  - Interpreter used (sh, cat, xargs, etc.)
  - Dispatch output (before interpreter)
  - Interpreter output (after interpreter)

EXAMPLE TRACE OUTPUT:
  === 2025-10-08 10:36:38 ===
  Command: vpn-switch.sh wireguard start privacy
  Interpreter: sh
  --- Dispatch output (before interpreter) ---
  wireguard connect 12345
  --- Interpreter output (after interpreter) ---
  [connection commands...]
  === End ===
